Name: Prototype Floor/Wall (ITC)
Review
Review section detail and 3D illustration from specification.
Sopradrain 20

Substrate: The substrate must be clean and free from loose materials or any construction debris prior to installing Sopradrain 20. Commencement of installation shall be taken as acceptance of the substrate by the applicator.
Sopradrain 20 must be installed vertically on the wall with nail fasterners from top edge to the bottom fillet.
Colphene BSW V

Substrate: The substarte must be smooth, dry and free of ice, snow or any other substance that may prevent the membrane from adhering effectively. Commencement of installation shall be taken as acceptance of the substrate by the applicator.
Colphene BSW V is installed in vertical strips of 5 m maximum onto acceptable substrate.
Colphene BSW V membrane is adhered to substrate by peeling off the silicone release film

Prime Colphene BSW V with Elastostic primer to increase the Colphene BSW V Adhesion. ELASTOCOL STICK can be applied with a brush, a roll or a spray can. The application surface must be thoroughly dry before applying the waterproofing membrane. Drying time will vary depending on air and surface temperature and humidity.
Install Colphene BSW V along floor/wall joint. 200mm lap onto prepared substrate/blinding.
Once installed, a pressure must be applied over the whole surface using a membrane roller to ensure good contact.
Install Colphene BSW V to wall, lap onto previously installed membrane with a lap of 150mm.
Membranes overlaps are sealed, by heat-welding, with a propane torch or using an electric hot-air welder.
Confirm all side laps are sealed and end laps by heat-welding the selvedge with a propane torch and minimum 2-10mm continuous bleed not smeared.
Side lap joints must be a minimum of 100 mm and end lap joints must be a minimum of 150 mm
Colphene BSW UNI NG

Substrate: The substrate must be smooth, dry and free of ice, snow or any other substance that may prevent the membrane from adhering effectively. Commencement of installation shall be taken as acceptance of the substrate by the applicator.
Ensure COLPHENE BSW UNI NG thickness is 4mm before the installation.
Lay CLOPHENE BSW UNIG NG loose on the prepared blinding floor using a roller for correct installation.
Install Colphene BSW UNI NG to floor butting up to floor and wall junction and to be lapped with existing COLPHENE BSW V to achieve 200mm lap.

Install Colphene BSW UNI NG reinforcing strip across floor/wall joint 150mm lap on wall, 250mm lap onto COLPHENE UNI NG on the floor. Ensure the COLPHENE UNI NG Reinfircement strip has smooth rounded edges at the floor/wall junction.
Stagger the end laps by a minimum of 300mm to avoid excessive membrane layering.

Install Colphene BSW UNI NG to reinforcing strip across wall membrane horizontal joint - 300mm lap over the the COLPHENE BSW V joint. Ensure the COLPHENE UNI NG Reinfircement strip has smooth rounded edges at the wall membrane horizontal joint.
Visual inspection of joint welds at cross laps.
Confirm no laps at capping beam construction joint
Confirm all side laps are sealed and end laps by heat-welding the selvedge with a propane torch and minimum 2-10mm continuous bleed not smeared.
